This page analyzes `Infrastructure Integrations` category of ingest using the known samples created by On-Host, Cloud, and Kubernetes integrations. Additional pages have been added to help analyze `Metric` category data generated by Prometheus and AWS CloudWatch Metric Stream integrations. 

*If you find a missing integration, please [open an issue](https://github.com/newrelic/quickstarts-dashboard-library/issues/new/choose) on our GitHub!*

![New Relic](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/93/Amazon_Web_Services_Logo.svg/1024px-Amazon_Web_Services_Logo.svg.png)

This page analyzes data coming from the various [AWS integrations](https://docs.newrelic.com/docs/integrations/amazon-integrations/aws-integrations-list/) available in New Relic. Data ingest for these integrations is most easily controlled in the individual service integration's [configuration settings](https://docs.newrelic.com/docs/integrations/infrastructure-integrations/cloud-integrations/configure-polling-frequency-data-collection-cloud-integrations/).

*This page DOES NOT represent data ingested from [CloudWatch Metric Streams](https://docs.newrelic.com/docs/integrations/amazon-integrations/aws-integrations-list/aws-metric-stream/), which is analyzed on a different page of this dashboard.*

This page analyzes data coming from both the [Prometheus OpenMetrics Integration (POMI)](https://docs.newrelic.com/docs/integrations/prometheus-integrations/get-started/send-prometheus-metric-data-new-relic/#OpenMetrics) and New Relic's [Remote Write Integration](https://docs.newrelic.com/docs/integrations/prometheus-integrations/get-started/send-prometheus-metric-data-new-relic/#remote-write). In the [Data Management Hub](https://one.newrelic.com/launcher/data-management-nerdlets.data-management-launcher), these are reflected in the `Metrics` category. Data ingest for these integrations is most easily controlled in the [Prometheus configuration](https://prometheus.io/docs/prometheus/latest/configuration/configuration/) by ensuring you only collect metrics you need using controls like scrape labels and relabel functions to filter data before shipping.
